subSubSection.paragraph:
Telson : Vesicle subspherical, not laterally compressed, narrower than metasoma V; anterodorsal lateral lobes prominent (
J. pintoi
) or reduced (
J. agamemnon
and
J. rochae
); lateral and ventral surfaces granular or smooth, with shallow ventromedian carina; subaculear tubercle present, prominent and spinoid (
J. agamemnon
) or vestigial (
J. pintoi
and
J. rochae
).
